@user4 @user3 You guys are doing it! And I'd be happy to help you with my experience.
Website: Take a look at @user5. It seems simple, looks good, and is open-source. I'll switch one of my websites to it before the next renewal.
Signal: Take a look at cal.com. It's an open-source calendar service with integrations that allow you to plan video calls with Element Call, JITSI, etc. Signal is also supported, but I haven't tried it yet to see if it's for messages or video.
I can recommend @user6. E2EE, decentralized, open-source.
